The paper focuses on image upscaling using convolutional networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of MuxOut layers and the interpretation of convolutional networks as adaptive filters suggest a focus on signal processing (cs.MM). The paper also introduces general purpose algorithms for analyzing networks, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of new upscalers that can sample the distribution of upscale aliases suggests a focus on generative models (cs.AI).
